Ugh, I hate dredging up old dross. Okay, you've probably seen Blok's weekly art polls, where he puts a number of subjects to a vote (usually his own characters, or propertied characters like Krystal). Originally, he used to accept a large number of suggestions which he pooled and pulled his subjects from randomly. If you were around for that, you'll recall that Teth'ra dominated that pool. C_F has/had always been a debbie downer in private, and Blok, in trying to be sympathetic to him, made more artwork of Teth - most of that was free artwork, which cut into Blok's bottom line. One of Cough's noisier lamentations was that he couldn't afford artwork (at the time). Cough wasn't shy about airing his gripes with the art, publicly nitpicking things about each piece often in ways that put Blok down. My understanding is that it was worse in private, and it didn't improve until Blok broke off any contact with Cough. In any case, he used his personal issues to guilt Blok out of art and pinups of Teth'ra, all of which greatly bolstered NoF's popularity, and unabashedly put him down with each release. Blok was trying to help him.

Cough's since apologized and this is all ancient history now; Blok's doing well, Cough might start writing again soon, and everyone's happy. Except Cough, but he's pathologically disconsolate. I'm happy he's gotten help and I'd love to see him return soon; NoF and TWIW are two of the highest-quality works of science fiction in the master, and Cough's got one of the best heads for the genre.
